Hint: Rate $=\mathrm{K}_2\left(\frac{\mathrm{~K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]^{\frac{3}{2}}$
Solution : Rate $=\mathrm{K}_2\left(\frac{\mathrm{~K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]^{\frac{3}{2}}$
so, $K=A e^{-\frac{E_0}{R T}}=A_2 e^{-\frac{E_2}{R T}} \times\left(\frac{A_1 e^{-\frac{E_1}{R T}}}{2 A_4 e^{\frac{E_i}{R T}}}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}$
$A=A_2\left(\frac{A_1}{2 A_4}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}$

Rate of reaction:
$\frac{\mathrm{d}\left[\mathrm{CH}_4\right]}{\mathrm{dt}}=\mathrm{K}_2\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]$

Now, by steady state approximation
$\begin{aligned}
\frac{\mathrm{d}\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]}{\mathrm{dt}}=0= & \mathrm{K}_1\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]-\mathrm{K}_2\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right] \\
& +\mathrm{K}_3\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{CHO}\right]-2 \mathrm{~K}_4\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]^2 \\
\frac{\mathrm{~d}\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{CHO}\right]}{\mathrm{dt}}= & 0=\mathrm{K}_2\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]-\mathrm{K}_3\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{CHO}\right]
\end{aligned}$
so, $\left[\dot{\mathrm{C}} \mathrm{H}_3\right]=\left(\frac{\mathrm{K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}$ \{rom (i) and (ii)\}
$\begin{aligned}
& \begin{aligned}
\frac{\mathrm{d}\left(\mathrm{CH}_4\right)}{\mathrm{dt}} & =\mathrm{K}_2\left[\frac{\mathrm{~K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]\right]^{\frac{1}{2}}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right] \\
& =\mathrm{K}_2\left(\frac{\mathrm{~K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}\left[\mathrm{CH}_3 \mathrm{CHO}\right]^{\frac{3}{2}}
\end{aligned} \\
& \text { so } \mathrm{K}=\mathrm{K}_2\left(\frac{\mathrm{~K}_1}{2 \mathrm{~K}_4}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}
\end{aligned}$
